            "answer_text": "A mole is a unit of measurement. One mole equals 6 x 10^23 atoms/molecules/whatever. So take the molecular mass of elemental oxygen - 16 grams per mole. Then convert from moles to grams: 1 mole elemental oxygen(16 grams O/1 mole) = 16 grams. Pretty basic question. Now if it was atmospheric oxygen O2 then it would be different because you would have two moles of oxygen which is 32 grams. Setup meetings with your chem teacher on google calendar to do practice problems that helps a lot. ",
